CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) allows you to apply various styles to text on a web page.
Here are some common CSS text styling properties and their descriptions:

1.Font Properties:
font-family: Specifies the typeface or font for the text.
font-size: Sets the size of the font.
font-weight: Defines the thickness of the characters (e.g., bold, normal).
font-style: Specifies the style of the font (e.g., italic, normal).
font-variant: Controls the usage of small caps or normal font.
font-stretch: Adjusts the width of the font.
line-height: Sets the height of a line of text.

2.text color
3.text align
P{
text_align: center;
}

4.Text Decoration:
text-decoration: Adds decorations like underline, overline, or line-through to text.
text-decoration-line: Specifies the type of text decoration.
text-decoration-color: Sets the color of the text decoration.
text-decoration-style: Sets the style of the text decoration.

5.Text Transformation:
text-transform: Controls the capitalization of text (uppercase, lowercase, capitalize).
h1 {
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

6.Letter Spacing and Word Spacing:
letter-spacing: Adjusts the space between characters.
word-spacing: Sets the space between words.
p {
  letter-spacing: 2px;
  word-spacing: 5px;
}

7.Text Shadow:
text-shadow: Adds a shadow to text.
It takes values for horizontal and vertical offsets, blur radius, and shadow color.
h2 {
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px #888;
}

8.Line Spacing:
line-height: Sets the height of a line of text, which can affect spacing between lines.
p {
  line-height: 1.5;
}

9.Text Overflow:
overflow: Controls how text overflows its container (e.g., hidden, scroll).
div {
  overflow: hidden;
}

10.Text Wrapping:**
   - `white-space`: Specifies how white space within text is handled (e.g., nowrap, normal).
p {
  white-space: nowrap;
}
